Seen within 30 seconds of Arriving at stakeout thanks to other birders! Yes!!! - continuing bird - seen by many - excellent looks at dark cap and yellowish body.  Small list for location as bird seen instantly!

In red berry tree where rbg grosbeaks seen. Derek got pictures. Then flew to euc above berry tree. Saw 4 or 5 times over 5-8 minutes. Loosely  warbling vireo.  Knew it wasn't a wRbling vireo as its back was yellowish-green with very grey hood with high contrast. Wanted to call it a red-eyed vireo but no contrast on face markings and eye not red. Got derek on bird and somehow he got picks. Picks seen by several (Oscar and Cedric) and called yellow green vireo. Also called out and Calvin had just arrived and his impression was Yellow green.  Absolutely amazing! Thought it was too windy but still went out and this was the reward.
